      "name": "Is vitamin D3 better than D2?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. D3 (cholecalciferol) is superior to D2 (ergocalciferol) for raising blood levels. D2 is cheaper and often prescribed in India, but studies show D3 is more bioavailable and produces more stable 25-hydroxy vitamin D levels. If supplementing, choose D3. Take it with dietary fat (olive oil, eggs, avocado) for optimal absorption. Many Indians take D on an empty stomach or with water, which reduces absorption significantly."
